    subject: "Polity & Governance", slug: "polity", title: "Indian Polity & Governance",
    blurb: "Master the Constitution and current-affairs polity for competitive exams.", emoji: "⚖️", accent: "#0891B2",
    order: 6, status: 'live', hasVideo: false,
    lessons: [
      { id: "polity-part1", title: "Indian Polity — Foundations of the Constitution", blurb: "The full static polity syllabus, from the Constituent Assembly to the judiciary.", order: 1, practiceHtmlPath: "/study/polity-part1.html", explanation: "<h3>Foundations of Indian Polity</h3><p>This module builds the static core of Indian Polity — the making of the Constitution and the institutions that flow from it, covering everything from the Preamble to the Supreme Court in one connected map.</p><ul><li><strong>Constitution basics:</strong> Constituent Assembly, Parts, 12 Schedules, and the Preamble (borrowed features and key amendments).</li><li><strong>Rights framework:</strong> Fundamental Rights (Part III), Directive Principles (Part IV), and Fundamental Duties (Part IV-A).</li><li><strong>Government structure:</strong> Union & State Executive (President, PM, Governor, CM), Parliament, Emergency provisions, and Panchayati Raj.</li><li><strong>Judiciary & watchdogs:</strong> Supreme Court and High Courts, constitutional bodies, landmark judgments, and Centre-State relations.</li></ul>" },
      { id: "ca-01-polity", title: "Polity & Governance — Current Affairs Revision", blurb: "Exam-ready revision blending core polity with 2024-25 governance developments.", order: 2, practiceHtmlPath: "/study/ca-01-polity.html", explanation: "<h3>Polity Current Affairs & Rapid Revision</h3><p>A high-yield revision node that fuses the static Constitution with recent governance news — built around month-wise facts, exam traps, and the articles that get asked most often.</p><ul><li><strong>Parliament & articles:</strong> Structure under Article 79 plus a drill of high-frequency constitutional articles and important Schedules.</li><li><strong>Amendments timeline:</strong> Visual sequence of key constitutional amendments to lock in numbers and years.</li><li><strong>Recent developments:</strong> Committees and commissions of 2024-25 and month-wise current-affairs facts.</li><li><strong>Trap-proofing:</strong> Common exam traps and the three Types of Emergency to avoid easy mistakes.</li></ul>" },
    ],
